<subSubSection id="28FB6564FFDBD655096BFB97144D306B" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" type="reference_group">
<emphasis id="5295EAFDFFDBD655096BFB9712923281" box="[801,957,1147,1176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDBD6550983FB9714443281" authority="Peters, 1867" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[969,1387,1147,1176]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">Miniopterus minor Peters, 1867</taxonomicName>
, “von der Kiuste von 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFDBD6550E08FB4F159232D9" box="[1090,1213,1187,1216]" name="Tanzania" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Zanzibar</collectingCountry>
[= from the coast of 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFDBD65509DCFB26155E32FE" box="[918,1137,1226,1255]" name="Zanzibar Island" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Zanzibar Island</collectingCountry>
, Tanzamal.” Traditionally, all small-sized 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDBD6550E96FB02145B3316" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[1244,1396,1262,1295]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Miniopterus</taxonomicName>
from continental Africa and nearbyislands, including 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFDBD65509FAFAD1157E3347" box="[944,1105,1341,1374]" name="Madagascar" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, have been included in 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDBD655091BFA8812FB339C" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[849,980,1380,1413]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">M. minor</taxonomicName>
. It was considered to have subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDBD655098BFA78151733B4" authorityName="Harrison" authorityYear="1959" box="[961,1080,1428,1453]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griveaudi">griveaudi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDBD6550E1AFA78158033B4" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[1104,1199,1428,1453]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="manavi">manavi</taxonomicName>
, and newton, which genetic studies separated as distinct species. At present, two subspecies are still recognized in continental Africa that might prove to be different species when studied in depth. Recently, it has also been found that 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDBD6550AB7F9BD1058306B" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[253,375,1617,1650]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">M. minor</taxonomicName>
from East Africa forms a paraphyletic group. Two subspecies recognized.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection id="28FB6564FFDBD6550AF4F99410B9312E" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" type="multiple">
<caption id="349E6667FFDBD6550AF4F99410B9312E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735264" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5735264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735264/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" targetBox="[126,717,800,1214]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFDBD6550AF4F99410B9312E" blockId="13.[187,1397,1577,3464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">
<emphasis id="5295EAFDFFDBD6550AF4F99413613080" box="[190,590,1656,1689]" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
M. m. 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDBD6550B5FF94C132130D8" authority="Peters, 1867" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[277,526,1696,1729]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">minor Peters, 1867</taxonomicName>
— coastal area in S 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFDBD655095CF94C124330D8" box="[790,876,1696,1729]" name="Kenya" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and N 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFDBD6550998F94C157F30D8" box="[978,1104,1696,1729]" name="Tanzania" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(including Unguja I in 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFDBD6550AA9F92B107130F1" box="[227,350,1735,1768]" name="Tanzania" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Zanzibar</collectingCountry>
Archipelago). M. m. occidentalisJuste &amp; Ibanez, 1992 — 
<collectingRegion id="A225F80DFFDBD65508BCF90312853109" box="[758,938,1775,1808]" country="Republic of the Congo" name="Bas-Congo" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">lower Congo</collectingRegion>
River in 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFDBD6550E64F903145E3109" box="[1070,1393,1775,1808]" name="Republic of the Congo" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFDBD6550AB6F8FA10BD312E" box="[252,402,1814,1847]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
